HOW WILL the Trump administration’s restrictions on American companies selling products to Huawei affect the Chinese telecoms giant? Can the world’s second biggest smartphone maker adapt to not doing business with America? Also, Michael Froman, a former US trade representative and the vice-chairman of MasterCard, discusses how private companies can promote freer trade. And Jennifer Eberhardt, a professor of psychology at Stanford University, explains the science of racial bias. Simon Long hosts. Runtime: 22mins    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn